# MDS Button Spacing Requirements

## Critical Rule

**Buttons must NEVER be flush against adjacent content.** Always ensure proper breathing room around buttons using margins or gaps.

## Minimum Spacing Requirements

### Buttons in Section Headers
When buttons appear in headers above tables or content sections:

```css
.section-header {
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem; /* Minimum 24px space below header */
}
```

### Horizontal Button Groups
Buttons placed side-by-side need gap spacing:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD - Use gap in flex containers */
.button-group {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem; /* 12px minimum between buttons */
}

/* ✅ GOOD - Use margin-right for inline buttons */
.table-actions .ui-Button {
  margin-right: 0.5rem; /* 8px minimum */
}
```

### Vertical Spacing Around Standalone Buttons
Buttons need breathing room from content above and below:

```css
/* ✅ GOOD - Margin around standalone buttons */
.action-button {
  margin-top: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
```

## Common Patterns

### ✅ GOOD - Section Header with Button

```tsx
<div className="section-header">
  <h2 className="section-title">Recent Projects</h2>
  <Button variant="primary">New Project</Button>
</div>
```

```css
.section-header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem; /* Space before table/content */
}
```

### ✅ GOOD - Action Buttons in Flex Container

```tsx
<div className="page-actions">
  <Button variant="tertiary">Cancel</Button>
  <Button variant="primary">Save</Button>
</div>
```

```css
.page-actions {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1rem; /* Space between buttons */
  margin-top: 2rem; /* Space above action group */
}
```

### ✅ GOOD - Buttons in Table Cells

```css
.table-actions {
  white-space: nowrap;
}

.table-actions .ui-Button {
  margin-right: 0.5rem;
}

.table-actions .ui-Button:last-child {
  margin-right: 0;
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Buttons Flush Against Content

```tsx
{/* No margin between button and table */}
<Button variant="primary">New Project</Button>
<table className="data-table">
  ...
</table>
```

```css
/* No spacing defined - BAD */
.button-container {
  display: flex;
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Insufficient Gap in Button Groups

```css
.button-group {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.25rem; /* Too small - BAD */
}
```

## Spacing Scale Reference

Use these minimum values:
- **Tight spacing** (table actions): `0.5rem` (8px)
- **Standard spacing** (button groups): `0.75rem - 1rem` (12-16px)
- **Section spacing** (headers, content separation): `1.5rem - 2rem` (24-32px)

## When Buttons Are in Headers

Headers that precede content (tables, cards, forms) need adequate bottom margin:
- **Minimum**: `1.5rem` (24px)
- **Recommended**: `1.5rem - 2rem` (24-32px)

This ensures the button and header don't visually merge with the content below.
